2 SENATE BILL 982
1 3–121.1.
2 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
3 (2) “Mutual insurance holding company” means a nonstock corporation
4 that:
5 (i) is incorporated in the State in accordance with a plan of
6 reorganization adopted and approved under this section; and
7 (ii) is the parent of a reorganized stock insurer.
8 (3) “Reorganized stock insurer” means the stock corporation into which a
9 mutual insurer is reorganized in accordance with a plan of reorganization adopted and
10 approved under this section.
11 (l) (1) A mutual insurance holding company:
12 (i) may not dissolve or liquidate except through proceedings under
13 Title 9 of this article OR IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 3–121.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE; and
14 (ii) shall be a party to any proceeding under Title 9 of this article
15 involving a reorganized stock insurer that is a subsidiary of the mutual insurance holding
16 company.
17 (2) In any proceeding under Title 9 involving a reorganized stock insurer
18 that is a subsidiary of a mutual insurance holding company, the assets of the mutual
19 insurance holding company shall be deemed to be assets of the estate of the reorganized
20 stock insurer for purposes of satisfying the claims of the reorganized stock insurer’s
21 policyholders.
22 (m) A mutual insurance holding company may become a stock insurer in
23 accordance with § 3–121 of this subtitle OR A MUTUAL INSURER IN ACCORDANCE WITH
24 § 3–121.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
25 3–121.2.
26 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
27 INDICATED.
28 (2) “MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY” MEANS A NONSTOCK
29 CORPORATION THAT:

SENATE BILL 982 3
1 (I) IS INCORPORATED IN THE STATE IN ACCORDANCE WITH A
2 PLAN OF REORGANIZATION ADOPTED AND APPROVED UNDER § 3–121.1 OF THIS
3 SUBTITLE; AND
4 (II) IS THE PARENT OF A REORGANIZED STOCK INSURER.
5 (3) “REORGANIZED STOCK INSURER” MEANS THE STOCK
6 CORPORATION INTO WHICH A MUTUAL INSURER IS REORGANIZED IN ACCORDANCE
7 WITH A PLAN OF REORGANIZATION ADOPTED AND APPROVED UNDER § 3–121.1 OF
8 THIS SUBTITLE.
9 (B) A MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY THAT, DIRECTLY OR
10 INDIRECTLY, OWNS 100% OF THE CAPITAL STOCK OF A REORGANIZED STOCK
11 INSURER MAY CONVERT ITS MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY SYSTEM INTO
12 A MUTUAL INSURER IN ACCORDANCE WITH A PLAN OF CONVERSION ADOPTED AND
13 APPROVED UNDER THIS SECTION.
14 (C) A PLAN OF CONVERSION SHALL PROVIDE THAT:
15 (1) ON THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF THE CONVERSION, THE MEMBERSHIP
16 INTERESTS IN THE MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY SHALL BECOME
17 NONTRANSFERABLE MEMBERSHIP INTERESTS IN THE CONVERTED MUTUAL
18 INSURER;
19 (2) FUTURE POLICYHOLDERS OF THE CONVERTED MUTUAL INSURER
20 SHALL BE MEMBERS OF THE CONVERTED MUTUAL INSURER;
21 (3) ON THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF THE CONVERSION, EACH POLICY OF
22 THE REORGANIZED STOCK INSURER SHALL REMAIN IN EFFECT AND MAY BE
23 ENDORSED;
24 (4) THE SHARES OF THE REORGANIZED STOCK INSURER AND ANY
25 INTERMEDIATE STOCK HOLDING COMPANY SHALL BE RETIRED;
26 (5) THE MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY AND ANY
27 INTERMEDIATE STOCK HOLDING COMPANY SHALL BE DISSOLVED BY FILING
28 ARTICLES OF DISSOLUTION WITH THE STATE DEPARTMENT OF ASSESSMENTS AND
29 TAXATION; AND
30 (6) THE CONVERTED MUTUAL INSURER SHALL HAVE SURPLUS FUNDS
31 THAT ARE REASONABLY ADEQUATE FOR THE SECURITY OF ITS POLICYHOLDERS.
32 (D) (1) A PLAN OF CONVERSION SHALL BE:

4 SENATE BILL 982
1 (I) APPROVED BY THE VOTE OF A MAJORITY OF THE BOARD OF
2 DIRECTORS OF THE MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY AND ANY
3 INTERMEDIATE STOCK HOLDING COMPANY;
4 (II) SUBMITTED TO A MEETING OF MEMBERS OF THE MUTUAL
5 INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY; AND
6 (III) APPROVED BY THE VOTE OF AT LEAST 75% OF THE
7 MEMBERS WHO VOTE ON THE PLAN OF CONVERSION IN PERSON, BY PROXY, OR BY
8 MAIL.
9 (2) NOTICE OF THE TIME, PLACE, AND PURPOSE OF THE MEETING OF
10 MEMBERS REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(II) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE
11 PROVIDED IN THE MANNER APPROVED BY THE COMMISSIONER.
12 (E) A PLAN OF CONVERSION SHALL BE SUBMITTED TO THE COMMISSIONER
13 FOR APPROVAL AT LEAST 60 DAYS BEFORE THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF THE
14 CONVERSION, TOGETHER WITH:
15 (1) AMENDMENTS TO THE ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION AND
16 BYLAWS OF THE REORGANIZED STOCK INSURER NECESSARY TO CONVERT TO A
17 MUTUAL INSURER;
18 (2) A 5–YEAR PLAN OF OPERATION FOR THE CONVERTED MUTUAL
19 INSURER, INCLUDING ANY PLANS FOR THE TRANSFER OF ASSETS OR LIABILITIES
20 FROM THE MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY OR ANY INTERMEDIATE
21 HOLDING COMPANY TO THE CONVERTED MUTUAL INSURER;
22 (3) A LIST OF THE OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS OF THE CONVERTED
23 MUTUAL INSURER;
24 (4) A BIOGRAPHICAL AFFIDAVIT OF EACH OFFICER AND DIRECTOR OF
25 THE CONVERTED MUTUAL INSURER; AND
26 (5) ANY OTHER DOCUMENTS OR INFORMATION REQUESTED BY THE
27 COMMISSIONER.
28 (F) (1) UNLESS DISAPPROVED BY THE COMMISSIONER, A PLAN OF
29 CONVERSION IS APPROVED:
30 (I) ON WRITTEN NOTICE FROM THE COMMISSIONER; OR

SENATE BILL 982 5
1 (II) 60 DAYS AFTER THE DATE THAT THE PLAN AND ALL
2 INFORMATION REQUIRED UNDER THIS SECTION AND UNDER ANY REGULATION
3 ADOPTED IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SECTION ARE SUBMITTED TO THE
4 COMMISSIONER.
5 (2) (I) SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE
6 COMMISSIONER SHALL APPROVE THE PLAN OF CONVERSION IF THE PLAN:
7 1. COMPLIES WITH THIS SECTION; AND
8 2. IS EQUITABLE TO THE MEMBERS OF THE MUTUAL
9 INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY AND THE POLICYHOLDERS OF THE REORGANIZED
10 STOCK INSURER.
11 (II) IN APPROVING A PLAN OF CONVERSION, THE
12 COMMISSIONER MAY IMPOSE ADDITIONAL CONDITIONS AND REQUIREMENTS THAT
13 THE COMMISSIONER DETERMINES ARE NECESSARY TO ACHIEVE THE PURPOSES OF
14 THIS SECTION.
15 (III) ON WRITTEN NOTICE TO THE MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING
16 COMPANY, THE COMMISSIONER MAY HOLD A HEARING NECESSARY TO DETERMINE
17 IF THE PLAN OF CONVERSION MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS PARAGRAPH.
18 (3) THE COMMISSIONER MAY RETAIN, AT THE EXPENSE OF THE
19 MUTUAL INSURANCE HOLDING COMPANY, A QUALIFIED EXPERT WHO IS NOT A PART
20 OF THE COMMISSIONER’S STAFF TO ASSIST IN REVIEWING THE PLAN OF
21 CONVERSION.
22 (G) THE COMMISSIONER MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS
23 SECTION.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2026.

